From 88491608e91f664d56cc6110c62c38e2073a9189 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 13:33:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Rebrand wizard UI to SustainOS visual identity

Repaint the assessment wizard from the dark provisional theme to the
SustainOS brand: warm cream canvas (#F5F4EF), white cards, indigo
(#6E6CFF) primary accent, lime (#C8F135) reserved for CTAs/accents, and
Poppins typography throughout.

Purely visual: only the <style> block and the font <link> change. All
markup, CSS class names, and JS logic are untouched, so behaviour is
identical. CSS variable names are kept (e.g. --purple now holds the
brand indigo) so existing var() references in both CSS and JS keep
working. Lime is remapped to indigo everywhere it was used as text
(unreadable on a light background) and kept only as button/accent fills.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01UiChTjRz9VhAHHURuFiz4m
